        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare genetic systemic or rheumatologic disease characterized by interstitial lung disease (often with pulmonary hemorrhage) and inflammatory arthritis associated with high-titer autoantibodies (including anti-nuclear and anti-neutrophil cytoplasmic antibodies and rheumatoid factor). Patients present from infancy to adolescence with tachypnea cough hemoptysis and/or joint pain. Some patients may also develop glomerular disease."
        },
